Run a Query Against the Index <L=r#p>¶</L><I=p>
Create a Query engine from the Index. A Query Engine is a generic interface that allows you to ask
question over your data. Here, the parameter  similarity_top_k  is set to 10. If you are using your own
documents, you can play around with this parameter.

In [ ]:

Copied! []

```python
query_engine = index.as_query_engine(similarity_top_k=10)
response = query_engine.query(
    "What was San Francisco's budget for Police in 2023?"
)
print(response)
