Context-Augmented OpenAI Agent <L=u#K>¶</L><I=K>
In this tutorial, we show you how to use our  ContextRetrieverOpenAIAgent  implementation to build an
agent on top of OpenAI's function API and store/index an arbitrary number of tools. Our
indexing/retrieval modules help to remove the complexity of having too many functions to fit in the
prompt.

Initial Setup <L=u#L>¶</L><I=L>
Here we setup a ContextRetrieverOpenAIAgent. This agent will perform retrieval first before calling any
tools. This can help ground the agent's tool picking and answering capabilities in context.

If you're opening this Notebook on colab, you will probably need to install LlamaIndex 🦙.

