llama_index.core.llms import ChatMessage from llama_index.core.tools import BaseTool, FunctionTool

Define Function Tools <L=G#J>¶</L><I=J>
We setup some trivial  multiply  and  add  tools. Note that you can define arbitrary functions and pass
it to the  FunctionTool  (which will process the docstring and parameter signature).

In [ ]:

Copied! []

```python
def multiply(a: int, b: int) -> int:
    """Multiply two integers and returns the result integer"""
    return a * b


multiply_tool = FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=multiply)
```

def multiply(a: int, b: int) -> int: """Multiply two integers and returns the result integer""" return
a * b multiply_tool = FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=multiply)

In [ ]:

Copied! []

```python
def add(a: int, b: int) -> int:
    """Add two integers and returns the result integer"""
    return a + b


add_tool = FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=add)
```

def add(a: int, b: int) -> int: """Add two integers and returns the result integer""" return a + b
add_tool = FunctionTool.from_defaults(fn=add)

